h4#creating-projects.page-header(style='color: #2980b9; font-size: 125%; font-weight: 500;')
  | Creating Projects 
  small (using the CLI)
p.lead
  | By using the CleverStack CLI's 
  code clever init
  |  command, creating new projects is easy and straight forward.
| {% highlight bash %}
| # for frontend & backend
| clever init my-app
| # backend only
| clever init my-app backend
| {% endhighlight %}
img(src='/assets/img/screenshots/clever-init-backend.png', width='100%')
br
br
p
  span.label.label-info Note
  |  After running this command you may be prompted to configure the module/s your installing, see 
  a(href='#configuration') Configuration
  |  for more information. Additionally you may be prompted to setup the seed data for the module/s your installing, see 
  a(href='/documentation/backend/models/#seed-data') Seed Data
  |  for more information.
br
.bs-callout.bs-callout-danger
  h4 Database creation
  p
    | If you are using SQL/ORM (aka MySQL, Postgre etc) then you will need to manually run the 
    code CREATE DATABASE
    |  command to create your database, the underlying library we use does not support this functionality.
.bs-callout.bs-callout-warning
  h4 Init running time
  p
    | This command may take awhile depending on your internet connection and computer specifications.
.bs-callout.bs-callout-warning
  h4 Command Failed Errors
  p
    | If you see a command failed error in your terminal/console after installing a module and seeing a message that states it's about to rebase or seed your database, it is highly likely that something is wrong with your configuration that you need to fix.
    br
    |   See 
    a(href='#configuration') Configuration
    |  and 
    a(href='#seed-data') Seed Data
    |  for information.
br
